<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/7–2050: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d88fn1">Repeated to London as 411.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-21T20:00:00-04:00">July 21,
                                    1950—8 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>399. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 385, July 20. While we
                            fully recognize importance of tripartite consultation on most matters
                            and wish to encourage it we wish definitely to play down tripartite
                            activity in <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> framework. We have
                            consistently made clear to the Fr our strong objection to any “political
                            standing group” and we would certainly not wish any such body
                            established in Wash since this wld completely undermine Deputies, whom
                            we regard as essential spark plug agency of whole <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> machinery. Naturally US–UK–Fr
                            Deputies will have much to discuss and will work closely together but
                            this shld be on strictly informal basis. Less said about it the
                            better.</p>
                        <p>Pls convey foregoing to Alphand.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>